{"title_page": "Mario Bertolo", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Mario Bertolo\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1929|1|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[San Vito al Tagliamento]], Italy\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2009|9|20|1929|1|28|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = Digoin, France\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n}}\n'''Mario Bertolo''' (28 January 1929 &ndash; 20 September 2009) was a French professional [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He rode in three editions of the [[Tour de France]].<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=1988 |title=Mario Bertolo |accessdate=7 February 2017 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Cycling archives|1988}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bertolo, Mario}}\n[[Category:1929 births]]\n[[Category:2009 deaths]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Friuli-Venezia Giulia]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{France-cycling-bio-1920s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Mario Bertolo\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1929|1|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[San Vito al Tagliamento]], Italy\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2009|9|20|1929|1|28|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = Digoin, France\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| 